<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

216
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,162
<font color="#808080">COP 1:</font> What are you doing?
<font color="#808080">COP 2:</font> Stay there! Don't move!

217
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,522
<font color="#808080">COP 1:</font> Identify yourself!
<font color="#808080">COP 2:</font> Get back here right now!

218
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,881
<font color="#D900D9">(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)</font>

219
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:24,162
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)</font>

220
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:33,286
Whoever it is, they couldn't
have made it very far.

221
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,044
I'll alert CDC to keep an eye out.

222
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,321
They're en route.

223
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:39,484
There's no way this attack was human.
You don't know that.

224
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,244
Don't know what?

225
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:44,204
The guy's shredded.
His throat was

226
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,408
in the gutter.
Just let me handle it.

227
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:49,040
What's to handle?
This has Lycan written all over it.

228
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:49,883
Detective,

229
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:53,567
when was the last time you heard
about a reported Lycan killing?

230
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:55,721
A couple years ago.

231
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,247
How many years
have you been with this department?

232
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,729
What? I've been here
for three months.

233
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,291
Exactly.

234
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:05,927
You question me less
until you know a bit more.

235
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:08,321
We clear?
Crystal.

236
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,891
<font color="#D900D9">(CELL PHONE RINGING)</font>

237
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:13,091
Detective Sebastian.

238
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,242
<font color="#808080">MAN <font color="#D900D9">(OVER PHONE)</font>:</font>
<i>Detective, we've just received a report.</i>

239
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:17,402
<i>There's been</i> a <i>disturbance
at Antigen Labs.</i>

240
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,210
<i>A witness says
there was an escape.</i>

241
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:20,930
<i>They said someone jumped</i>

242
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:23,242
<i>out of a window.
This is a priority</i>

243
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,401
<i>investigation.</i>

244
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,090
<i>We need you over there ASAP.</i>

245
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,765
We're on our way.

246
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:30,161
Hey, let's go.
Johnson, you're the lead.

247
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:32,089
<font color="#808080">JOHNSON:</font>
You got it, detective. Will do.

248
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:49,931
Who's in charge?

249
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:55,811
There's a Detective Sebastian
here to see you, sir.

250
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,404
Where is he?

251
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:01,642
In the lobby, sir.

252
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:06,731
<font color="#808080">LANE:</font>
<i>You'll be relieved to know</i>

253
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,723
the situation is well under control.

254
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:11,201
What happened?
I repeat, well under control.

255
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,050
I repeat, what happened?

256
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:16,882
Ah, yes, there are
reports to be filed.

257
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,881
One of our test subjects
attempted to escape.

258
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:22,202
We were forced to put it down.

259
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,931
So nothing got out?
Only a stray bullet.

260
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,771
And the test subject?
Flash-burned.

261
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,002
Will that be all?

262
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:31,961
A few things to attend to.
You could imagine.

263
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,323
Doctor, we received
an anonymous call

264
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:36,847
that something else
escaped through a window.

265
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,800
Detective, our mission at Antigen
is to develop ways of preventing

266
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:44,760
infection, not releasing it
into the general population.

267
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,006
I lost my son to this disease.

268
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:51,562
There's no room for error with me
when it comes to the safety of

269
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:54,041
the public.
If something had escaped,

270
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:56,362
the authorities
would have been notified.

271
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:58,124
You are an authority,
are you not?

272
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,843
Now, if you'll excuse me...

273
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,242
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

274
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:28,882
The guy in charge
says it's nothing. Let's go.

275
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:31,884
Yeah, and he's full of shit.
Look at this.

276
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:34,891
Want me to report it, sir?

277
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,650
No. I'll do it.

278
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,962
I don't mind.
I can do it for you.

279
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:42,886
All right, sir.

280
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,844
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

281
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,248
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

282
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:10,605
The prisoner that helped me escape,
the one you called Subject 2,

283
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:12,921
was it a hybrid?

284
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:15,401
Yes.

285
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,085
What were you doing with us?

286
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,161
We...

287
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:22,770
We help the government
identify the infected.

288
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:25,611
We were using your DNA
to try to find a cure

289
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:28,081
to prevent another outbreak.

290
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,810
You were told that I would

291
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,769
lead you to the hybrid. Why?

292
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:35,331
Subject 2 is restricted information.

293
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,130
I don't have the clearance.

294
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,244
You're lying.

295
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,886
No! Aah!

296
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:44,405
No, please!

297
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:45,402
All I know is

298
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:47,130
there's a connection
between you.

299
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:48,801
Your brain waves

300
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,769
fall into sync when you're close

301
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:51,807
to each other.

302
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,200
You can see through
each other's eyes!

303
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,441
Please don't!

304
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,090
I'm the one who let you go!

305
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,130
Now we're even.

306
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:02,206
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

307
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:14,205
<font color="#D900D9">(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)</font>

308
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:20,202
<font color="#D900D9">(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)</font>

309
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,168
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

310
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,644
<font color="#808080">COP 1:</font>
What the hell was that?

311
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:37,009
<font color="#808080">COP 2:</font>
Creepy is what.

312
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:38,924
I'm calling it in.
Let's go.

313
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:23,768
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

314
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:26,522
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

315
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:28,723
Shit.

316
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,048
Doni.

317
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,281
Why not?

318
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,205
We're the same.

319
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,205
Why are you following me?

320
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:50,089
We monitor the police frequencies.

321
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:51,801
Well?

322
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:54,770
Do you know what attacked
that human under the bridge?

323
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,886
No.

324
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:57,882
<font color="#D900D9">(LYCANS GROWLING)</font>

325
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:01,725
Lycans.

326
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,086
What remains of them, yes.

327
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:07,762
They've been hiding
down here like rats

328
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,842
since the Purge.

329
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,288
Diseased and starving, they rarely
show themselves above ground.

330
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:15,211
Which means that something
has got them riled up.

331
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,450
Something you're not telling me.

332
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,531
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING IN DISTANCE)</font>

333
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:22,762
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

334
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:35,082
Michael!

335
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:46,810
<font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOTS)</font>

336
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,769
Do you know her?

337
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,160
No.

338
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,885
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING IN DISTANCE)</font>

339
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:29,370
They will come back in numbers.

340
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:32,604
We can't leave her here.

341
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,602
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

342
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:38,522
Come on.

343
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,166
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
Let's try the van.

344
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,289
Get in. Move! Move!

345
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,402
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTS)</font>

346
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:09,403
<font color="#D900D9">(TIRES SCREECHING)</font>

347
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:14,045
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

348
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:18,530
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
Three of them behind us.

349
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,211
<font color="#D900D9">(CAR HORN HONKS)</font>

350
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,209
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
Go!

351
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:34,768
<font color="#D900D9">(EVE SCREAMS)</font>

352
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:35,688
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
Hurry, Selene!

353
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:37,001
They're getting in the back!

354
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:42,367
<font color="#D900D9">(DAVID YELLING)</font>

355
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,803
Fucking piece of shit!

356
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,731
<font color="#D900D9">(EVE GRUNTING AND SCREAMING)</font>

357
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:55,811
The girl! They're taking her!

358
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:01,568
<font color="#D900D9">(EVE SCREAMS)</font>

359
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:06,010
<font color="#D900D9">(ROARS)</font>

360
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,684
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

361
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:32,611
You drive.

362
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,842
<font color="#D900D9">(POLICE SIRENS WAILING
IN DISTANCE)</font>

363
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,082
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

364
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:56,962
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

365
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,964
She's not healing.

366
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:23,521
We have a doctor
that can help her at our coven.

367
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:25,768
<font color="#808080">EVE:</font>
How did you

368
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,126
find me?

369
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:30,805
What's your name?

370
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:33,244
Subject 2.

371
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:36,205
And you are Subject 1.

372
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,208
I freed you.

373
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:43,568
Do you not know who I am?

374
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:47,770
They told me that I had no mother,

375
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:50,161
that she died when I was born.

376
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,768
I never believed it. I...

377
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:56,487
I felt you.

378
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:58,927
Saw images through your eyes.

379
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:02,131
But then someone outside my door,

380
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:07,450
they said since I was no longer
a child, the wait was over,

381
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:10,764
that I'd be dead soon.

382
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:14,290
And that my own mother,
right next door,

383
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:17,531
would never even know
I'd existed.

384
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,641
What did they tell you
of your father?

385
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:24,484
They must have told you
something.

386
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,688
Do you see images through him?

387
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:28,400
No.

388
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:30,171
Only you.

389
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:36,002
<font color="#808080">EVE:</font>
No, please!

390
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,046
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLS)</font>

391
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,162
<font color="#808080">LIDA:</font> <i>She's never stepped
foot outside the lab.</i>

392
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,845
How can she possibly survive?

393
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:55,004
I understand the risk of reporting
her escape to the authorities.

394
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,286
No record of her birth.

395
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:58,801
Questions will be asked.
I'm well aware of that.

396
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:01,008
But if she dies,
all our years of research...

397
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:02,844
Rather than tell me
how to do my job,

398
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:06,004
why not take a look at your
own professional conduct?

399
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:08,845
And how your continual need
to endow this creature

400
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:13,050
with human traits has led to the
laxness of its security protocols.

401
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:15,851
It's not a human being, Lida!
It's not your child.

402
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,201
It's not to be coddled.

403
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,362
It's a blight of nature.

404
00:30:23,080 --> 00:30:25,321
Stop worrying.
It'll come back to us.

405
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:36,964
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER CRASHES)</font>

406
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,564
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

407
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:21,166
<font color="#D900D9">(DAVID GRUNTS)</font>

408
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,684
Get Olivia at once.

409
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:07,131
<font color="#808080">THOMAS <font color="#D900D9">(IN RUSSIAN)</font>:</font>
Again you break my rules. Why?

410
00:32:07,320 --> 00:32:09,448
<font color="#808080">DAVID <font color="#D900D9">(IN RUSSIAN)</font>:</font>
She was attacked.

411
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,001
She is not healing.

412
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,606
And for this
you compromise our safety?

413
00:32:13,760 --> 00:32:14,522
<font color="#808080">SELENE <font color="#D900D9">(IN RUSSIAN)</font>:</font>
You have

414
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,808
no reason to fear us.

415
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:21,803
<font color="#D900D9">(IN ENGLISH)</font> Do you think I'm foolish
enough to take you at your word?

416
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:24,207
No reason

417
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:27,170
to fear a Death Dealer
who fell in love with a Lycan,

418
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:29,368
who murdered two of our elders,

419
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,882
and who, at every turn,
has betrayed

420
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:33,326
her own kind.

421
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:37,210
Do you know who this is?

422
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:40,043
<font color="#D900D9">(IN ENGLISH)</font>
Yes.

423
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:43,888
But it was we
who betrayed her, Father.

424
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:46,921
Let her through.

425
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:50,805
She's not healing.

426
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,441
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

427
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,762
She was attacked by
a lower Lycan.

428
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:05,641
Two hours ago.

429
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,203
<font color="#808080">OLIVIA:</font>
Her cell repair is

430
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:13,729
active but weakened.

431
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,721
She has no

432
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,490
origin bite marks

433
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,125
or scars.

434
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:27,087
I've never seen a child
like this before.

435
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:29,882
When did you last feed?

436
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,571
Feed?

437
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:34,524
Give her blood.

438
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:44,048
<font color="#808080">OLIVIA:</font>
Child,

439
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,565
you must.

440
00:34:03,640 --> 00:34:04,926
Slowly.

441
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:07,085
Slowly.

442
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:10,921
There.

443
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,764
There, now.

444
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,530
She's healing.

445
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:23,442
And quickly.
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font> Good.

446
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:25,443
Take her to my room.
She needs to rest.

447
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:26,601
No.

448
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:29,291
Look at the eyes.

449
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:41,688
<font color="#808080">OLIVIA:</font>
I never believed it.

450
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,684
They do exist.

451
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:47,407
This is not one of us.

452
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:50,001
No, it's something more, Father.

453
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,602
What do you know of her?

454
00:34:57,160 --> 00:35:00,050
<font color="#D900D9">(IN ENGLISH)</font> I was held captive
at a place called Antigen.

455
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:03,881
One of the other prisoners
freed me.

456
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:06,324
I believed it was Michael Corvin

457
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:09,006
the only hybrid
I knew existed at that time.

458
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:11,208
Yes, yes, your Lycan lover,
long dead.

459
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:13,044
What is this, then?

460
00:35:14,640 --> 00:35:16,369
None of your concern.

461
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:19,890
As soon as she regains
her strength, I will leave with her.

462
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,282
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

463
00:35:58,200 --> 00:35:59,406
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
I used to hear stories

464
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:00,925
of the Death Dealers.

465
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:05,761
That they were a thing of the past,

466
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:07,809
never to return.

467
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:11,049
I'm glad they were wrong.

468
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:14,563
You knew who I am...

469
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:18,722
and yet you still
brought me here.

470
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:22,690
Thank you.

471
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,649
You're a fighter.

472
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,526
We could use more like you
to teach us.

473
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:28,442
I'm not sure

474
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,045
your father would agree.

475
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:33,921
There was a time when he would have.
That's why he dislikes you so much.

476
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:38,324
I think it reminds him of the days
when he defended us with fire and steel

477
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:42,041
rather than hollow words.
He knows how much we need you.

478
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:46,564
I'm not a leader.
But you fight for what you believe in.

479
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:48,761
You always have.

480
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:49,807
I don't know

481
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,325
what I believe in any more.

482
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:54,046
I don't recognize this world.

483
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:56,089
But you haven't changed.

484
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:59,240
I saw it in your eyes
when you looked at the child.

485
00:37:00,160 --> 00:37:02,686
You will protect her.

486
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,126
It's in your blood.

487
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:05,890
It's who you are.

488
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,926
When you leave, take me with you.

489
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:55,442
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

490
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:16,283
You distrust me.

491
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:26,009
Of course you do.
I made you feel unwelcome.

492
00:38:26,160 --> 00:38:28,288
And for that, I'm sorry.

493
00:38:30,160 --> 00:38:31,685
Ah.

494
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,764
Those eyes,

495
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:37,364
they're special.

496
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:42,721
I know exactly what you are.

497
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:56,086
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
<i>My father says that,</i>

498
00:38:56,240 --> 00:38:59,687
should we survive as a species,
these relics will help

499
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:02,411
our descendants know
who we were and how we lived.

500
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:04,164
And what do you say?

501
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:06,727
That if we continue to live
as we do now,

502
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:09,724
then we disgrace the past
and don't deserve a future.

503
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:12,247
We must resist the humans

504
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,848
wherever and whenever possible.

505
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:17,207
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font>
Between the first and second Purges,

506
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:22,568
Lycan youth rallied in the same way
against the prudence of their elders.

507
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:26,281
Their calls for violent action
carried the day.

508
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:27,965
The result?

509
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:31,004
The Werewolves are nearly extinct.

510
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:34,884
Is that what you wish for us,
extinction?

511
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:36,641
Yet you bring

512
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:39,087
her offspring into our home.
Do you honestly

513
00:39:39,240 --> 00:39:42,210
believe the humans
will allow her to remain free?

514
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:44,483
They will hunt her down
at any expense.

515
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:47,564
Then we can help protect them.
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> Protect them?

516
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,929
They leave tonight.

517
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:50,929
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
This isn't

518
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:51,763
prudence.

519
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:53,809
This is cowardice, plain and simple.

520
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,689
How dare you?

521
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,124
How dare you

522
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:02,441
do so little?

523
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:36,121
I dreamt of the day we would meet.

524
00:40:38,960 --> 00:40:41,281
Like a silly little girl.

525
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:50,410
You're as cold as one already dead.

526
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,485
Yesterday

527
00:40:57,120 --> 00:40:59,282
I was with your father.

528
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:05,762
He was only a little further away
from me than you are now.

529
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:09,809
I went to sleep.

530
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:13,802
And when I awoke the next day,

531
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:17,129
I learned that, overnight,

532
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:20,527
12 years had passed.

533
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:25,369
And instead of the only man
I've ever loved,

534
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:29,206
there stood a girl with his eyes.

535
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:36,087
My heart is not cold.

536
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:37,924
It's broken.

537
00:41:42,040 --> 00:41:43,769
I'm so sorry.

538
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:55,446
What is it?

539
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,045
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font>

540
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:58,721
They're here.

541
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:02,281
Stay here. Wait for me.

542
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:03,885
No, take me with you.

543
00:42:04,080 --> 00:42:05,241
Please.

544
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:08,722
I won't let anyone hurt you. I promise.

545
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:09,967
Lock the door.

546
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,485
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

547
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:14,042
Everybody to the shelter. Now!

548
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:15,440
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHATTERING)</font>

549
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:16,966
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
No!

550
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:19,088
Prepare the armory.

551
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:21,322
Do as I say! Go, 90!

552
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:24,767
Pay heed to me!

553
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:28,083
No! We stand and we fight.

554
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:30,009
<font color="#D900D9">(VAMPIRES SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY)</font>

555
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:46,446
No! Have you no sense?

556
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:51,602
Stop this now!

557
00:42:53,040 --> 00:42:56,123
We lived safely for years and you
brought humans into this coven.

558
00:42:56,520 --> 00:42:57,442
They want the girl.

559
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:59,284
They'll stop at nothing
to get her.

560
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:02,330
This day was bound to come,
with or without us.

561
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:05,086
Let's move!
Munitions, let's go! Everyone!

562
00:43:05,240 --> 00:43:06,526
Are you mad?

563
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:09,968
We have no more than a handful
of fighters. We will be annihilated!

564
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:12,410
And what's your plan, Father?

565
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:14,130
Let's go! Now!

566
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,331
Where are you going?
To get her away from here.

567
00:43:18,480 --> 00:43:21,211
He's right. I shouldn't have come.
He doesn't understand.

568
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,886
The humans will follow us out.
Hold them off till then.

569
00:43:25,080 --> 00:43:26,320
They're only here for her.

570
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:29,323
She's more powerful
than any of us.

571
00:43:29,480 --> 00:43:31,164
They fear the day
she discovers it.

572
00:43:32,320 --> 00:43:34,049
I have to get her out of here.

573
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,209
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font>

574
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:10,725
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

575
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:13,644
Lycan!

576
00:44:15,480 --> 00:44:16,402
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

577
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:19,091
Silver ammunition!

578
00:44:19,240 --> 00:44:20,082
Now!

579
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:21,447
Defend the second

580
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:22,283
rotunda!

581
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:23,771
Move! Move!

582
00:44:24,360 --> 00:44:25,600
<font color="#D900D9">(LYCANS GROWLING)</font>

583
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:26,966
<font color="#D900D9">(VAMPIRES GRUNTING)</font>

584
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:46,162
<font color="#D900D9">(POUNDING ON DOOR)</font>

585
00:45:08,040 --> 00:45:09,405
<font color="#808080">SELENE:</font>
Open the door!

586
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:12,248
Let's go.

587
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:13,602
<font color="#D900D9">(LYCAN GROWLS)</font>

588
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:16,287
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

589
00:45:17,560 --> 00:45:18,288
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

590
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:35,327
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

591
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:37,566
Move! Move!

592
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:09,166
<font color="#D900D9">(LYCAN ROARING)</font>

593
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:19,240
We need to go.

594
00:46:19,560 --> 00:46:20,447
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

595
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:28,248
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

596
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:34,007
<font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOT)</font>

597
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,247
<font color="#D900D9">(ROARING IN DISTANCE)</font>

598
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,001
<font color="#808080">DAVID:</font>
What the hell was that?

599
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:47,441
<font color="#D900D9">(VAMPIRES SCREAMING)</font>

600
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:51,688
Take her somewhere safe.
No.

601
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:53,330
Take her. Go.

602
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:11,848
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

603
00:47:16,520 --> 00:47:18,010
<font color="#D900D9">(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)</font>

604
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:24,645
<font color="#D900D9">(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING
AND LYCAN GROWLING)</font>

605
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:31,245
<font color="#D900D9">(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)</font>

606
00:47:34,840 --> 00:47:35,841
<font color="#D900D9">(LYCAN SCREAMS)</font>

607
00:47:40,120 --> 00:47:42,122
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font>

608
00:47:58,400 --> 00:48:00,402
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

609
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:39,681
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

610
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:49,643
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

611
00:49:00,720 --> 00:49:02,290
<font color="#D900D9">(SELENE GRUNTING)</font>

612
00:49:35,240 --> 00:49:36,730
Where is she?

613
00:49:37,200 --> 00:49:38,690
They took her.

614
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:41,523
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font>
They accepted her.

615
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:45,322
As a gift from me.

616
00:49:48,120 --> 00:49:49,963
<font color="#D900D9">(EVE PANTING)</font>

617
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:55,802
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

618
00:50:25,080 --> 00:50:26,411
Do you know what you've done?

619
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:29,000
Do you have any idea?

620
00:50:29,160 --> 00:50:31,401
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font>
What would you have had me do?

621
00:50:31,600 --> 00:50:35,889
Fight to the last to protect the
very one who brought this upon us?

622
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:37,407
We're defeated.

623
00:50:38,400 --> 00:50:40,448
Our coven is destroyed.
My son

624
00:50:40,640 --> 00:50:41,448
is dead.

625
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:43,570
Because of you.

626
00:50:44,640 --> 00:50:45,801
Why?

627
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:48,731
Because he helped that

628
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:50,530
child of yours.

629
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:52,762
If they kill her, so be it.

630
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:56,288
Your son died because
he was fighting for all of you.

631
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:00,082
Because he knew that running
is not survival.

632
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:03,564
Those were Lycans.

633
00:51:03,720 --> 00:51:06,803
Not extinct.
More powerful than ever.

634
00:51:07,200 --> 00:51:10,124
That thing was more than twice
the size of any Lycan I've seen.

635
00:51:11,920 --> 00:51:12,762
They risked

636
00:51:12,960 --> 00:51:17,090
showing themselves after more than
a decade in hiding because of her.

637
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:19,527
And you handed her over to them.

638
00:51:21,440 --> 00:51:22,441
She is the last

639
00:51:22,640 --> 00:51:26,645
direct descendant
of Alexander Corvinus.

640
00:51:27,240 --> 00:51:30,528
The only hybrid child
that has ever existed.

641
00:51:32,960 --> 00:51:35,406
Whatever it is the Lycans
want from her,

642
00:51:36,440 --> 00:51:38,761
your son knew it was
worth dying for.

643
00:51:45,720 --> 00:51:47,051
What are you doing?

644
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:09,601
<font color="#D900D9">(VAMPIRES MURMURING)</font>

645
00:52:14,800 --> 00:52:16,245
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

646
00:52:16,520 --> 00:52:17,851
David.

647
00:52:18,520 --> 00:52:20,682
<font color="#D900D9">(DAVID'S HEART BEATING)</font>

648
00:52:49,360 --> 00:52:51,362
<font color="#D900D9">(♪♪♪)</font>

649
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:33,644
<font color="#808080">SELENE:</font>
A force of two dozen Lycans

650
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:36,963
attacked and destroyed
one of our covens last night.

651
00:53:38,920 --> 00:53:40,206
You're not surprised.

652
00:53:42,600 --> 00:53:44,284
You knew the Lycans
were not extinct.

653
00:53:45,240 --> 00:53:47,163
How?
Just a feeling.

654
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:49,602
I'm not good with feelings.

655
00:53:49,760 --> 00:53:51,603
I want to know how.

656
00:53:51,840 --> 00:53:54,047
This is not the place for this.

657
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:56,285
And you're not gonna kill me.

658
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:57,441
Really?

659
00:53:57,600 --> 00:53:58,726
No.

660
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:01,207
Because you wouldn't need
a fucking gun to do it.

661
00:54:03,800 --> 00:54:05,040
<font color="#808080">SEBASTIAN:</font>
<i>A few years ago,</i>

662
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:08,124
the government declared
"mission accomplished" on Lycans.

663
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:10,521
The feds announced that
we were to only focus

664
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:12,370
on your kind now.

665
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:15,844
Three months ago,
a friend of mine sent me this.

666
00:54:17,120 --> 00:54:20,761
It arrived two days after he was found
hanging from his own ceiling fan.

667
00:54:23,320 --> 00:54:25,448
Two hundred suspected
Lycan captures.

668
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:27,125
Every case was investigated.

669
00:54:27,320 --> 00:54:29,482
Every blood test came back negative.

670
00:54:29,640 --> 00:54:30,926
My friend began to wonder:

671
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:34,567
Were they all false leads or was
someone trying to protect the Lycans?

672
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:38,331
Helping them replenish their packs,
letting them regroup.

673
00:54:38,520 --> 00:54:40,488
What about your own department?

674
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:46,841
They have my daughter.
All I care about is getting her back.

675
00:54:48,520 --> 00:54:52,969
If you're protecting someone, I don't care.
I'm not after them. I just want her.

676
00:54:53,280 --> 00:54:54,566
No.

677
00:54:55,520 --> 00:54:59,445
Even if there are others in my department,
they wouldn't have the authority.

678
00:54:59,760 --> 00:55:01,285
This goes much higher.

679
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:04,327
I believe, all the way to the top.

680
00:55:05,880 --> 00:55:06,847
Or to the bottom.

681
00:55:07,400 --> 00:55:08,686
<font color="#808080">SEBASTIAN:</font>
What do you mean?

682
00:55:09,760 --> 00:55:11,888
Who administers the tests?

683
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:16,162
<font color="#808080">LANE:</font> We're a bit short on time, so
if you please, take a look at these.

684
00:55:17,040 --> 00:55:19,520
This schedule takes you
from the moment we adjourn

685
00:55:19,680 --> 00:55:22,126
through to the final manufacture
of the vaccine.

686
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:27,524
If we stick to this plan, inoculations
should begin within three months.

687
00:55:27,680 --> 00:55:29,523
Any questions, now's the time.

688
00:55:29,720 --> 00:55:32,963
After today's surgery, there will be
no communication between us

689
00:55:33,120 --> 00:55:35,361
until we meet again
in the inoculation center.

690
00:55:35,600 --> 00:55:37,011
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font>
Doctor, in terms

691
00:55:37,160 --> 00:55:38,525
of your test subject,

692
00:55:38,680 --> 00:55:41,411
he continues to demonstrate
immunity to silver?

693
00:55:41,560 --> 00:55:42,891
Absolutely.

694
00:55:43,200 --> 00:55:47,489
And additional inoculations,
administered only as a precaution,

695
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:49,722
triggered side effects
we never imagined.

696
00:55:50,080 --> 00:55:51,241
Vast increases

697
00:55:51,400 --> 00:55:53,641
in strength, muscle mass,

698
00:55:53,800 --> 00:55:55,484
self-healing.

699
00:55:55,680 --> 00:55:56,806
Stamina.

700
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:00,331
You said she was essential
to our research.

701
00:56:01,080 --> 00:56:03,560
Yes, and will continue to be.
<font color="#808080">LIDA:</font> How?

702
00:56:04,440 --> 00:56:05,965
By vivisecting her?

703
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:08,124
You weren't meant to have that.

704
00:56:08,280 --> 00:56:09,930
<font color="#808080">LIDA:</font>
I cared for this little girl

705
00:56:10,480 --> 00:56:13,768
all these years,
and you expect me to sit by

706
00:56:14,240 --> 00:56:16,766
while you...
